                  </persName>
            . Wife and the prisoner were drinking together at my house on the 5th of April. Wife fell asleep; while he was asleep, the prisoner desired me to draw him a pint of beer: when he had drank the beer he went out, and did not return again.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was drinking with the prosecutor at the Butcher's Arms. I had occasion to go to the necessary, and there I found the watch: the next day I pawned the watch to get some things out of pawn.</p>
               <p>Q. to Wise. Was you ever at the necessary?</p>
               <p>Wise. No, I never stirred off my seat.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called two witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
